âœ… 1. What is ListView.builder?
ðŸ‘‰ English:

ListView.builder is a widget that creates a scrollable list.
It builds items only when they are visible, so it is faster for long lists.

ListView.builder(
  itemCount: 10,   // à¤•à¤¿à¤¤à¥€ items à¤¹à¤µà¥‡à¤¤
  itemBuilder: (context, index) {
    return ListTile(
      title: Text("Item $index"),
    );
  },
);

âœ… 1. What is ListView.separated?
ðŸ‘‰ English:

ListView.separated creates a list where you can add a separator (divider, spacing, line) between each item.

ListView.separated(
  itemCount: 5,
  itemBuilder: (context, index) {
    return ListTile(
      leading: Icon(Icons.person),
      title: Text("Name $index"),
      subtitle: Text("Subtitle $index"),
      trailing: Icon(Icons.arrow_forward_ios),
      onTap: () {},
    );
  },
  separatorBuilder: (context, index) {
    return Divider(
      thickness: 1,
      color: Colors.grey,
    );
  },
);
